data.value: Kilkenny is a city in the province of Leinster in south-east Ireland that is the county town of County Kilkenny. The town’s population is 8,711, but the majority live outside the town boundary: the 2011 Irish census gave the total population of the town and environs as 24,423.

data.name: label4.Text
data.value: Ingredients: ● 3 large onions ● 4 large Carrots ● stewing steak (meat) ● 8 large potatoes ● salt & pepper How to make: ● Wash and cut onions into moderate size chunks and add to the pot. ● Wash carrots and cut into chunks. ● Wash and peel the potatoes then cut each one in half. ● Slice the meat into smaller pieces. ● Add the potatoes and then add meat. ● Heat pots until water boils, and then add carrots. ● Keep on a low boil and stir every now and then until vegetables are cooked. ● Add salt and paper. ● Serve hot!
